    "body": "This is a general CMake CUDA language hint to use the CXX compiler has host compiler for NVCC. Seems like a good default since we do not express the CUDA compiler in Spack otherwise yet (e.g. no `self.compiler.cuda` or `self.compiler.cudahostcxx`).\r\n\r\ncc @svenevs\r\n\r\n- [ ] also add [`CUDACXX`](https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.14/envvar/CUDACXX.html)?\r\n- [ ] Maybe also add to mixing class `lib/spack/spack/build_systems/cuda.py`?",
